<h4>New Goal</h4>
<h5>Key Features</h5>
<ul>
		<li>General Information</li>
		<li>Date Boundaries</li>
		<li>Goal Specifics</li>
</ul>

<h5>General Information</h5>
<p>General information can be entered to identify the goal. A unique name
and complete description will be useful when identifying multiple goals on the
goal index page.</p>
<h5>Date Boundaries</h5>
<p>Goals are only active throughout a particular date range. You may specify
a custom date range or use one of the generic ranges provided.</p>
<h5>Goal Specifics</h5>
<p>The goal specific are used to establish your goal. Currently total
distance, average pace, and total time may be used to establish your goal. Once
two of the three fields are input, the third will be automatically calculated.
This is done so that goals are not accidentally created that cannot be
completed.</p>